<br>
Reply 2) - 5) <br>
<br>
This server was created as the &quot;role-playing&quot; preferred server for a reason.  The ruleset was developed<br>
here for a reason.  These 2 things have gone hand in hand.  When it no longer has a majority of players who care about role-playing, then you'll be seeing the &quot;uber euro guilds&quot;, and all the other things you didn't like elsewhere, because then we'll end up just like the other servers.<br>
<br>
So you end up coming across as someone who wants all the advantages of being *near* the roleplayers, now if only you didn't actually have to cope with them.... oh dear.....<br>
<br>
Instead of complaining about RPers, you should be out there thanking them every goddamned day for letting this &quot;experiment&quot; of Verant's go as far and as well as it has.  You should be Roleplaying your little heart out, at least 5 minutes a day, when it doesn't cost you anything else, to help maintain the atmosphere we have here.<br>
<br>
You should be hanging out in the newbie yards, helping people by your own behavior learn what it means to roleplay here, and what might be expected of them, not as you suggested in your original post, some kind of condescending patronage, but folks who actually enjoy taking time with newbies whose only &quot;crime&quot; is that they don't have a clue to help get one.<br>
<br>
And to answer the subject/topic of your post, some RP'ers are soo lame because out of any given group of people, some of them are lame.  Take 1000 ballet fans, and some of them are lame.  Take 1000 football players and some of them are lame.  Take 1000 network news anchors and most of the them are lame (ha-ha).  Take 1000 politicians and 998 of them are lame.<br>
<br>
I myself don't try to go around *dictating* to others how they should do their roleplaying.  But people who use /shout for inappropriate topics, /auction anywhere but cities or for inappropriate topics, etc., are going to get on my bad side regardless of whether they're RPing at the moment or not.<br>
<br>
And people who *demand* my attention and assistance in dungeons and then put down my role-playing that I'm trying to do with them as a result of their own behavior - well, 'dey don get nuttin'.<br>
<br>
