<br>
Its not a hard thing to respect the intent of the original channels. Disrespecting that intent, disrespects the roleplayers on this server, since the system is set up for them. Complaining and arguing about your right to misuse a system at others expense will get no support from me.<br>
<br>
Even the complaints regarding roleplayers attitude belongs on other servers. <br>
<br>
/ooc: If someone in a restaurant is shouting stupid comments so that everyone on the block can hear it - I will complain. Both to the restaurant owners and to the police eventually, if it continues. The person who made the shouts is not able to stand behind a &quot;I can so I will&quot; attitude; disturbing the peace is disturbing the peace and it punished accordingly. Just because we have a limited police force on FV, doesn't inherently mean you are right. People here are just able to be more vocal about their RP wants and needs than on other servers. Ooc shouts and auctions interfere heavily with their game play, and completely unnecessarily.<br>
